{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b19076c4-7337-4f32-b875-1b0034eb95e8","content":"Two things change with xUnit v3 + MTP (`UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner=true`):\n\n1. **`--filter` is VSTest syntax** — MTP uses `--treenode-filter` instead, passed after `--`.\n2. **Syntax is path-based**, not property-based.\n\nYour old filter:\n```\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nTranslates to:\n```\ndotnet test -- --treenode-filter \"/**/*IntegrationTests*/**[Category=Smoke]\"\n```\n\n**Syntax breakdown:**\n\n| Concept | VSTest `--filter` | MTP `--treenode-filter` |\n|---|---|---|\n| FQN contains | `FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests` | `/**/*IntegrationTests*/**` (path wildcard) |\n| Trait match | `Category=Smoke` | `[Category=Smoke]` (bracket property) |\n| AND | `&` | Combine path + `[prop]` inline |\n\nThe `--` separator tells `dotnet test` to forward the remaining args to the MTP runner. No code changes needed — your `[Trait(\"Category\", \"Smoke\")]` attributes work the same in xUnit v3.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"501780f5-9809-40af-88c3-578d87e023c3","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is migrating from xUnit v2 to xUnit v3 with MTP (Microsoft Testing Platform). There are two key changes:\n\n1. **Filter syntax changes with MTP**: When `UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner` is true, `dotnet test` uses the Microsoft Testing Platform instead of VSTest. The `--filter` syntax changes from VSTest's filter format to MTP's `--treenode-filter` format.\n\n2. **The old filter**: `--filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"`\n   - `FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests` means FQN contains \"IntegrationTests\"\n   - `Category=Smoke` means Trait \"Category\" equals \"Smoke\"\n   - `&` is AND\n\nWith MTP, the filtering works differently—instead of VSTest's filter syntax, it uses `--treenode-filter` with path-based filtering where properties are specified as `[key=value]` and the test's fully qualified name maps to its node path in the test tree.\n\nWhen running `dotnet test` with MTP enabled, the `--filter` flag still works but gets translated through a bridge layer, though this translation isn't always perfect for xUnit v3. Alternatively, I can use `dotnet test -- --treenode-filter` to pass MTP-native filters directly, which uses a hierarchy separated by `/` with traits specified as `[trait=value]`. I'm working through the exact syntax for the Microsoft Testing Platform's treenode filter—it uses path separators with wildcards and property filters in brackets, so combining a name pattern like `/**/*IntegrationTests*` with a category filter `[Category=Smoke]` should give me the right syntax, though I need to verify whether it's `/**` or just `/*` between segments to properly match tests within that class. that get passed to the test runner itself.","outputTokens":1461,"requestId":"0C08:3A1531:27481A:2DEDEE:69F006C6"},"id":"cd0e5260-baa0-4ca8-958a-114b29b64188","timestamp":"2026-04-28T01:01:23.083Z","parentId":"a19e10e2-bcfe-490e-92bb-77a95d2237b4"}
